@title: INDENTATION

@description: Each indentation level must be done by using 4 spaces.
No tabulations may be used for indentation.
When entering a new scope (e.g.: control structure), the indentation level must
 be incremented.

```c
// OK
int main(void)
{
	char letter = 'H';
	int number = 14;
	if (letter == 'H') {
		my_putchar ('U');
	} else if (letter == 'G') {
		if (number != 10)
			my_putchar ('O') ;
		else {
			my_putnbr(97) ;
		}
	}
}

// Incorrect
int main(void)
{
int i;
}


// Incorrect
int main (void)
{
    if (true) {
    return (0);
    }
}
```

